{"key":"processedPost-13994588","value":{"id":13994588,"first":13993690,"last":13994588,"when":1298216728,"utime":"02/20/11 05:45 PM","cleanedPost":"You can stack jars in a PC.&nbsp; What will happen is that it will take much longer for steam to begin venting as you're warming it up.&nbsp; It will also take longer to come up to pressure because you have so much more material to heat up.&nbsp; However, once it's fully up to pressure, you can use the same time.&nbsp; If it's BRF jars, use 1 hour.&nbsp; If quart jars of grains, use 90 minutes, but you don't start the timer until 15 psi is reached.<br />It should go without saying that when using jars or spawn bags in a pressure cooker, steam should be able to permeate all the way around each substrate.&nbsp; In other words, don't put two large spawn bags up against each other or one on top of the other without a spacer which allows steam to penetrate the gap between them.<br />RR"}}